This script demonstrates a simple and efficient way to programmatically download the Elliptic dataset from Kaggle using the 
`kagglehub` library. It ensures that the latest version of the dataset is retrieved and provides the local file path 
for immediate use in data analysis or machine learning workflows.The approach is clean and reproducible, making it particularly 
useful for projects involving blockchain analytics, fraud detection, or financial transaction modeling. Automating dataset access 
in this manner helps streamline the data pipeline and improves project scalability. Overall, this is a well-structured starting point for 
integrating external datasets into a Python-based data science environment.
